00:32:29.180 --> 00:32:30.590 align:middle line:90%
to solve your problem.

00:32:30.590 --> 00:32:34.130 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, so that's why we don't
see this object very often, say

00:32:34.130 --> 00:32:39.220 align:middle line:84%
when you discuss special
relativity or other things.

00:32:39.220 --> 00:32:43.820 align:middle line:84%
But here, it plays a
very important role

00:32:43.820 --> 00:32:45.770 align:middle line:84%
that in quantum
field theory, this

00:32:45.770 --> 00:32:50.990 align:middle line:84%
is the operator which
generates the boost symmetry.

00:32:50.990 --> 00:32:56.270 align:middle line:84%
If you want to do a boost
in your Hilbert space,

00:32:56.270 --> 00:32:57.930 align:middle line:90%
that's the operator to do it.

00:32:57.930 --> 00:33:01.060 align:middle line:90%


00:33:01.060 --> 00:33:02.050 align:middle line:90%
Other questions?

00:33:02.050 --> 00:33:10.180 align:middle line:90%


00:33:10.180 --> 00:33:11.670 align:middle line:90%
Good.

00:33:11.670 --> 00:33:13.320 align:middle line:90%
Yeah, so in your pset--

00:33:13.320 --> 00:33:15.960 align:middle line:90%


00:33:15.960 --> 00:33:18.580 align:middle line:84%
yeah, another example
is the phase rotation.

00:33:18.580 --> 00:33:20.770 align:middle line:84%
Let me just very
